  <div class='medium-8 columns'><div class="webex-group">
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>What is the distance between the two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (2, 4)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (5, 4)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system?</p>
<p><input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-8cb010037bd5cd1cb0392d31cb34f4c0' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='Y0FREmw='/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distance <span class="math inline">\(d\)</span> of <span class="math inline">\(p\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q\)</span> is given by <span class="math inline">\(d^2 = (p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2\)</span> (Pythagorean formula).</p>
<p>Hence <span class="math inline">\(d = \sqrt{(p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2} =
  \sqrt{(2 - 5)^2 + (4 - 4)^2}
   = 3\)</span>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>What is the distance between the two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (3, 2)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (5, 5)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system?</p>
<p><input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-5cc18fd8db762bd301dad3605bbceb56' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='bkFQHw5WUho5'/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distance <span class="math inline">\(d\)</span> of <span class="math inline">\(p\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q\)</span> is given by <span class="math inline">\(d^2 = (p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2\)</span> (Pythagorean formula).</p>
<p>Hence <span class="math inline">\(d = \sqrt{(p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2} =
  \sqrt{(3 - 5)^2 + (2 - 5)^2}
   = 3.606\)</span>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>What is the distance between the two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (3, 2)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (4, 1)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system?</p>
<p><input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-ece32f6a6ec59e21e7f19c4c120351d9' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='PkFUHQZXAkNr'/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distance <span class="math inline">\(d\)</span> of <span class="math inline">\(p\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q\)</span> is given by <span class="math inline">\(d^2 = (p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2\)</span> (Pythagorean formula).</p>
<p>Hence <span class="math inline">\(d = \sqrt{(p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2} =
  \sqrt{(3 - 4)^2 + (2 - 1)^2}
   = 1.414\)</span>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
